Here's how to implement this in .NET MAUI Shell:

```csharp
public partial class EditProductPage : ContentPage
{
    private bool _hasUnsavedChanges;

    public EditProductPage()
    {
        InitializeComponent();

        // Custom back button
        Shell.SetBackButtonBehavior(this, new BackButtonBehavior
        {
            Text = "Cancel",
            Command = new Command(async () => await TryNavigateBack())
        });
    }

    // Intercept hardware/gesture back navigation
    protected override bool OnBackButtonPressed()
    {
        if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            // Fire-and-forget the async dialog; return true to cancel navigation
            MainThread.BeginInvokeOnMainThread(async () => await TryNavigateBack());
            return true; // cancel default back
        }
        return false; // allow default back
    }

    private async Task TryNavigateBack()
    {
        if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            bool leave = await DisplayAlert(
                "Unsaved Changes",
                "You have unsaved changes. Discard and go back?",
                "Discard", "Stay");

            if (!leave)
                return; // user chose to stay
        }

        await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
    }
}
```

**Key points:**

- **`OnBackButtonPressed()`** – intercepts Android hardware/gesture back. Return `true` to cancel navigation.
- **`BackButtonBehavior`** – replaces the shell back arrow with a "Cancel" button and routes taps through your command.
- **iOS swipe-back** – `BackButtonBehavior.Command` handles the toolbar button, but to block the iOS swipe gesture you may also need:

```csharp
Shell.SetPresentationMode(this, PresentationMode.ModalAnimated);
```

or disable the gesture in a platform-specific handler:

```csharp
#if IOS
Microsoft.Maui.Handlers.PageHandler.Mapper.AppendToMapping("DisableSwipeBack", (handler, view) =>
{
    if (view is EditProductPage)
        handler.ViewController?.NavigationController
            ?.InteractivePopGestureRecognizer?.SetEnabled(false);
});
#endif
```

Set `_hasUnsavedChanges = true` whenever form fields change (e.g., via property change tracking or binding).
